I clearly didn't know.

50:07.120 --> 50:09.248
Fuck, let's go. Let's go!

50:11.480 --> 50:13.323
We ordered some drinks

50:13.600 --> 50:15.364
and we're going to drink them.

50:26.440 --> 50:29.046
His face, man.
Did you see his fucking face?

50:29.120 --> 50:30.884
You punch like a fucking kangaroo.

50:30.960 --> 50:33.930
I seen one once in a circus,
you punch like that.

50:35.160 --> 50:36.969
All right, anyway,
I need a fucking drink.

50:37.040 --> 50:39.771
- It's on you.
-It's on me? You just got paid.

50:39.840 --> 50:41.251
Yeah, from you.

50:41.680 --> 50:44.001
You can get a whisky,
maybe even a dark mild.

50:48.320 --> 50:51.529
Fucking hell,
it's packed in here, isn't it?

50:52.360 --> 50:53.566
So it's as easy as that?

50:53.640 --> 50:56.962
Easy as that, John boy.
London, you wouldn't believe it.

50:57.240 --> 50:58.765
Finn, stick your head in a bucket.

50:58.840 --> 51:00.330
No.

51:00.520 --> 51:02.727
The women, John boy, the women...

51:03.280 --> 51:05.726
I've got this one,
she's a dancer, right?

51:05.800 --> 51:07.609
She can do things with her...

51:10.920 --> 51:13.207
If Finn would just piss off,
I'd explain a little bit better.

51:13.480 --> 51:15.767
Well, if it's so good, why are you here?

51:16.640 --> 51:18.449
Decent pints.

51:18.640 --> 51:20.324
The cockneys can't get that right.

51:20.400 --> 51:22.767
He misses us, Finn, that's what it is.

51:24.000 --> 51:27.209
Here they are, look, junior Peaky boys.

51:30.760 --> 51:32.762
What's happened to you?
You been scrapping?

51:34.280 --> 51:35.770
Some idiots at the Marquis of Lorne.

51:35.840 --> 51:38.605
Tried to stop me and Isaiah
from drinking, but it's all right.

51:38.800 --> 51:40.211
We fought them off.

51:40.640 --> 51:42.529
Arthur, we had to stand
our ground and we did.

51:43.760 --> 51:46.206
The Marquis, eh? Where's your dad?

51:47.320 --> 51:49.049
- Preaching.
-Right.

51:52.840 --> 51:54.251
Don't nick any of me chips, Finn!

51:54.320 --> 51:56.288
- Where are you going?
- We won't be long.

51:58.920 --> 52:00.410
Where are they going?

52:00.480 --> 52:01.720
The Marquis of Lorne.

52:03.040 --> 52:04.405
Shame.

52:04.480 --> 52:06.050
It was a nice pub.

54:01.800 --> 54:04.451
Eh-up. Bet the big bastard got cut.

54:07.520 --> 54:09.090
You didn't have to do that for me.

54:09.160 --> 54:10.650
We didn't do it for you, Michael.

54:10.720 --> 54:12.882
We did it for the good name
of the company.

54:13.960 --> 54:16.361
None of this happened, all right?

54:16.440 --> 54:18.408
Come on, let's go and get that drink.

54:46.120 --> 54:47.770
The date has been set.

54:49.720 --> 54:51.688
Three weeks from today.

54:55.240 --> 54:56.844
You checked out his house?

54:58.640 --> 55:00.369
There's coppers all over it.

55:01.800 --> 55:03.689
You'll take care of them?

55:03.960 --> 55:05.962
No. That would arouse suspicion.

55:07.520 --> 55:09.249
You'll have to deal with them yourself.

55:12.080 --> 55:13.844
And if a copper gets killed?

55:16.160 --> 55:20.051
There will be no consequences
for you, I have given you my word.

55:20.120 --> 55:22.009
Which I know to be worthless.

55:24.040 --> 55:27.965
That is why I have been settling
my affairs in the event of my death.

55:31.560 --> 55:34.450
And making your peace
with God, perhaps?

55:36.760 --> 55:38.489
Well, good luck with that.

55:43.640 --> 55:47.486
I have made arrangements
with men I trust.

55:49.360 --> 55:51.522
If I should die,

55:51.600 --> 55:53.045
then you will die.

55:54.600 --> 55:56.011
Know that.

57:29.520 --> 57:31.568
Ritz Hotel.

57:31.640 --> 57:33.085
London, Piccadilly.

57:42.840 --> 57:44.046
Hello?

57:45.800 --> 57:47.245
<i>Hello?</i>

57:53.440 --> 57:55.090
- Who was that?
-Call got cut.

57:55.640 --> 57:57.927
<i>I guess the telephone lines
in England are not so good, huh?</i>

57:58.000 --> 57:59.001
Hm.

58:01.000 --> 58:11.001
